# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you
#   want to suggest a specific tooling version, but see:
#   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54315206/should-we-gitignore-the-python-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1181, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're building something that is installed as a package, you might look into Pipfile.lock.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Using Poetry, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#Poetry.lock

